    <img class="nhsuk-image__img nhsuk-u-margin-top-7 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-7" src="/service-manual/assets/binary-question-long.png" alt="Screenshot of NHS Manage your referral login">


  <p>Filter questions ask a short question first - often a Yes No question. They let you:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>get people to the questions that apply to them - use them early on</li>
    <li>avoid optional questions, because users only answer the questions that apply to them</li>
    <li>simplify long questions</li>
  </ul>

    <h2>Be clear what "Yes" and "No" mean</h2>
<p>Rather than simply offering "Yes" or "No" options, be clear.</p>

<div class="app-example nhsuk-u-margin-top-7 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-7">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  {{ radios({
    "idPrefix": "example",
    "name": "example",
    "fieldset": {
      "legend": {
        "text": "Can we contact you by email about research?",
        "classes": "nhsuk-fieldset__legend--m"
      }
    },
    "items": [
      {
        "value": "yes",
        "text": "Yes, you can contact me by email about research"
      },
      {
        "value": "no",
        "text": "No, do not contact me about research"
      }
    ]
  }) }}
</div>

<p>In a simple Yes No question, "No" could also mean:<p>
<ul>
  <li>"No, do not contact me by email"</li>
  <li>"No, do not contact me at all"</li>
</ul>

<p>You may not need to collect answers to filter questions.</p>
<p>Filter questions are useful but there are some things to bear in mind, especially with Yes No questions.</p>

<h2>Be careful with binary choices</h2>
<p>There are often more options than you think.

<h3>Let users answer "I don't know" or "I'm not sure"</h3>

<p>In the research example above, users might want to say:</p>
<ul>
  <li>"I don't understand the question"</li>
  <li>"I only want to know about x research"</li>
</ul>

<div class="app-example nhsuk-u-margin-top-7 nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-7">
  <strong class="nhsuk-tag nhsuk-tag--dark-grey app-example__heading">Example</strong>
  {{ radios({
    "idPrefix": "example",
    "name": "example",
    "fieldset": {
      "legend": {
        "text": "Can we contact you by email about research?",
        "classes": "nhsuk-fieldset__legend--m"
      }
    },
    "items": [
      {
        "value": "yes",
        "text": "Yes, you can contact me by email about research"
      },
      {
        "value": "no",
        "text": "No, do not contact me about research"
      },
      {
        "value": "Understand",
        "text": "I don't understand the question"
      }
    ]
  }) }}
</div>

<p>You could include alternatives like:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Other</li>
  <li>Not sure because ...</li>
  <li>Something else</li>
</ul>



<p>Sometimes you can test this by leaving a space for people to type in.</p>

